title: Photostat, "Female Head, Three-Quarter View  to Left"
description:
The drawing medium, brown in the present object, may have been black in the original.

The eyes, glancing upward and to the left, are placed beneath shaded lids and brows. The outline of the face on the left indicates a high cheekbone and sharp chin; a dark mark beneath full lips may depict a cleft. Wavy hair, cascading to the shoulders, completes the design.

tombstone.epitaph:
Photostat, "Female Head, Three-Quarter View  to Left".
14.3 x 14.3 cm (5 5/8 x 5 5/8 in.). Gift of Ellen Gustav Jensen. 1956-47-67.
